<br>
I agree 200%, single player sucks.  Multiplayer is what I'm talking about.  Log on to a good &quot;OLTL&quot; (One life to live) server and I wouldn't be suprised if you started liking the game a little more.  Where team work actually matters, and you actually value your life.  Unless you prefer the unlimited life stuff.<br>
<br>
<br>
I recently started playing BG2, and I honestly have to say that I'd prefer it over Fallout any day. (Note the &quot;I's&quot; in that sentence.)<br>
<br>
There's far more depth to it than what there first appears.  Not even 1/6th of the way through the game and I've found more side quests (Completed some, still working on others).  Knowing when and how to use spells requires more thought than the simple AP system of Fallout.<br>
<br>
Maybe if I could control the other characters in my party when playing Fallout, I'd like the combat a little more.<br>
<br>
<br>
&lt;font size=&quot;+6&quot;&gt;I&lt;/font&gt; personally prefer the real time combat of Baldur's Gate, with the option of pausing and planning your attack out at your will.  I've been in too many fights where I'm forced to look at my screen for more than what I'd like waiting for the computer to finish moving all of the characters.<br>
<br>
<br>
I really haven't noticed being forced to finish anything in BG anymore than what you are in Fallout.<br>
<br>
<br>
I'm not saying Fallout is better than BG, or BG is better than Fallout.  And I'm not trying to &quot;win a contest&quot; as Yang puts it.  I'm stating my opinion on the game, and simply saying which I prefer. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub38.ezboard.com/utheyanger.showPublicProfile?language=EN>The Yanger </A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www1.iswest.com/theyanger/y.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br>  Posts: 1809<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(3/10/02 4:52:03 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm14.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=250.topic&index=27>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: NeverWinter Nights and the Monk</span><hr size=1> Oh no, not a single life. You can do that in damn near every FPS released in the last 2 years. I could just play CS or whatever, more fun thx.<br>
